                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Decided to find out the value of the potime avoidance mod to an enchanter since I've never seen one done for any caster class and wanted to see if this mod was worth spending on.
<br />

<br />
Details:
<br />
Mob was a Needlescale Hatchling from the trap next to zonein in PoE.
<br />
Attack was off except to break mez initially.
<br />
Buffs of importance to this parse were Virtue and Shield of Maelin.
<br />
Healing was done by my cleric alt.
<br />
Agro was maintained during the entire fight using near-chain tash, and slow every ~1.5minutes.
<br />
Mob was slowed during entire duration.
<br />
An arbitrary time of 1 hour for each set chosen.
<br />
YALP was used to parse info.
<br />
I have max def skills and AAs.
<br />

<br />
No Avoidance Mod:
<br />
1074 AC
<br />
192 Agi
<br />
Total time: 3732 seconds
<br />
Total damage: 431542
<br />
Mob DPS: 115.63 
<br />
Mob Hit %: 78.85% (1652 hits)
<br />
Mob Miss %: 19.95% (418 misses)
<br />
Dodge %: 1.19% (25 dodges)
<br />

<br />
10 Avoidance Mod:
<br />
1088 AC
<br />
174 Agi
<br />
Total time: 3713 seconds
<br />
Total damage: 435332
<br />
Mob DPS: 117.24
<br />
Mob Hit %: 78.89% (1644 hits)
<br />
Mob Miss %: 18.23% (380 misses)
<br />
Dodge %: 2.88% (60 dodges)
<br />

<br />
My conclusions:
<br />
The avoidance mod seems to increase dodges, but at the cost of reducing number of misses.  The tradeoff seems to be one to one so the value of this mod looks to be quite dubious.  One hour for each set seems long enough because that's probably the most any enchanter will be tanking over an exp/raid session.  
<br />

<br />
This isn't the end of it though, 10 avoidance isn't a lot by today's standards.  I didn't post the histogram, but seems to show a mitigation improvement with the 10 avoidance set.  It doesn't make any sense to call it "avoidance" if it affects mitigation, but it's worth looking into.  I'd like to see what numbers some of the casters with 50+ avoidance come up with, and maybe some against GoD mobs.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Montaigne on Tue Apr 06, 2004 3:31 pm; edited 1 time in total</span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
